ABUJA – The President of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan has said the year 2020 will usher in robust peace and economic growth for the benefit of all Nigerians. This is even as the Deputy President of the Senate, Ovie Omo-Agege charged Nigerians to build bridges of friendship across political, ethnic and religious lines. Lawan, in a statement by his Special Adviser on Media, Ola Awoniyi,congratulated Nigerians on witnessing the end of 2019 and the beginning of the year 2020, just as he hailed the resilience of Nigerians in their commitment to the unity and prosperity of the country and support for the administration of President Muhammadu Buhari. He said: “I have no doubt in my mind that with the timely passage of the budget, restoration of the January to December financial year and other amendments recently made to our laws by the ninth National Assembly, the economy will enjoy significant growth in the new year.” Powered by RubiQube Ad Network The president of the senate assured Nigerians that the National Assembly will continue to do its best to make things better for the people through enactment of people-oriented legislations. He added that the National Assembly will endeavour to sustain the harmonious working relationship with other arms of government for the smooth administration of the country and benefit of the people. In his New Year message, Omo-Agege said that the new year is a time for rebirth and optimism, even as he was upbeat that if Nigerians work resolutely as one, the challenges facing the country would be surmounted. In a statement, by his Special Adviser, Media and Publicity, Yomi Odunuga, the deputy president of the senate urged Nigerians to “recognize the beautiful and positive diversity of our nation, embrace the vital truth that our diversity is our strength.” He called for continued support for the Muhammadu Buhari-led administration, in not only maintaining the unity of the country but also delivering on the Next Level Agenda to Nigerians.